{{wikipedia|dab=craft (disambiguation)|craft}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|cræft|lang=ang}} (compare Old Frisian {{term|creft|lang=ofs}}), with the sense shift to "skill, art" probably leading to the related "[[trade]]", thus the first nautical use (1671) relating to smaller vessels (nautical use for tools of fishing trade unclear).

